memories.title: The Ask
memories.text:
We were in the cinema
I wasn't watching the film
I was watching my hand

I wasn't sure if I could hold your hand
I didn't know if I had the right
But I wanted to feel your hand
just once

I waited, hesitated, then tried
And when you didn't pull away
that moment, right before our fingers touched
felt like the beginning of something I'd been waiting for

memories.title: Same Screen
memories.text:
We watched so many movies together
two screens, one moment
You were far, but somehowâ€¦ I felt close

It felt like you were sitting right beside me
I remember your messages more than the scenes
Your words made the silence feel warm

I kept waiting for your thoughts
feeling like time paused
just to let us exist in the same dream

Those nights, I didn't fall for the movie
I fell for you

memories.title: 7olm
memories.text:
You sent me a voice note
Singing
Not loud. Not perfect
But your voice felt like it knew where my heart was

It didn't just carry the song
it carried a piece of you
In that moment
I didn't hear a song
I heard something softer

My chest tightened
Tears came, no reason needed
I felt love
The quiet kind
The real kind

memories.title: Jp Kat3jbini
memories.text:
I don't remember the movie
I only remember the message I sent
"Jp kat3jbini"

It was quiet. Simple. Almost shy
But in that moment
everything paused
the screen, the sound, my thoughts

That line was my way of saying
"I'm already yours"
without saying too much

And when you answered...
I knew something had started
something we never named
but both felt

memories.title: Reflection in Your Eyes
memories.text:
I remember the cinema lights on your face
The screen glowing in your eyes
I wasn't watching the movie anymore
I was watching the reflection in your eyes

The way you looked at the screen
so focused, so soft
it made me feel like I was inside the story

That moment wasn't loud
But it stayed
Like your eyes had recorded it for me

memories.title: Our List
memories.text:
We'll keep adding to it
Little things we dream up together
A place to go
A meal to cook

It won't be perfect
But it'll be ours

One day, we'll look at that list
and realize we didn't just write plans
we wrote a life

memories.title: Holding Hands
memories.text:
We held hands through the whole movie
Not just for a moment
No tension. No fear
Just warmth, stillness, and you

I don't remember what the film was about
But I remember how still your hand felt in mine
That silence between our fingers
said more than anything we could've spoken

memories.title: First Date
memories.text:
Our first real moment
Not a screen. Not a message
Just you. Just me

We met at the cinema
But I wasn't nervous about the movie
I was nervous about seeing you
for real

I remember how you looked
What you wore
The way you smiled when you saw me

That day, I knew

This was the beginning of something real
